# Architecture Boundaries

Follow README architecture and module responsibilities.

## Required flow
- UI (Compose) -> ViewModel -> domain/use-case -> repository interface -> service interface -> API/SDK.
- Repositories expose domain interfaces from `repositories/*/domain`.
- Services expose domain interfaces from `services/*/domain`.

## Rules
- Keep UI state and side effects coordinated by ViewModel.
- Throw/propagate domain-level errors as project conventions require (`DomainError` pattern).
- Keep feature code inside `features/`
- Shared feature concerns belong to `features/common/<feature name>`
- Code potentially shared by all features belongs to `features/common`
- Use `core:design` for visual tokens/components instead of duplicating styles.

## Guardrails
- No boundary leaks (UI directly calling service implementations, etc.).
- No new cross-module coupling without matching existing patterns.
